Task 2¶

  • Find at least three sets of spatial data, in Shapefile, zipped Shapefile, GeoJSON, or other supported formats. If you have well-prepared data from previous works, you can also use them. You can use the three zipped files in the Code folder on Dropbox, which are the new electoral district maps in NYS.
  • Import those data into GeoDataFrame using geopandas. Take one dataset as an example, show the specific types of the entire dataframe, the geometry column, and individual geometry object. This also helps you get familiar with pandas subsetting (choose rows and columns from the tabular data).
  • Export all three into a SINGLE geopackage file (geodatabase). Note that the single geopackage file should have three layers inside, not three layers in three separate geopackage files.

Import Data

In [ ]:
#import data using geopandas
sen22 = geopandas.read_file('./SEN22_June_03_2022.zip', driver = 'zip')
con22 = geopandas.read_file('./CON22_June_03_2022.zip', driver = 'zip')
ably22 = geopandas.read_file('./2022assembly_shape_file.zip', driver = 'zip')

Export

In [ ]:
#Export all three into a SINGLE geopackage file (geodatabase)
sen22.to_file("package.gpkg", layer ='sen22', driver = "GPKG")
con22.to_file("package.gpkg", layer ='con22', driver = "GPKG")
ably22.to_file("package.gpkg", layer ='ably22', driver = "GPKG")
